# 04-DATABASE - Database Design Rules

## Database Rules Directory

This directory contains all database design and management rules for Agent Player.

## Files Structure

### Core Database Files
- `schema-design.mdc` - Database schema design rules
- `performance.mdc` - Database performance optimization
- `migrations.mdc` - Migration management strategies
- `security.mdc` - Database security requirements
- `backup.mdc` - Backup and recovery procedures

## Purpose

Define database standards for:
- PostgreSQL schema design
- Performance optimization
- Data integrity
- Security measures
- Backup procedures

## Rules Coverage
- 37 tables across 11 domains
- Index strategies
- Constraint management
- Migration procedures
- Security measures

## MANDATORY Database Standards
- All tables must have primary keys
- Foreign key constraints required for relationships
- Indexes on all frequently queried columns
- NOT NULL constraints where appropriate
- Check constraints for data validation
- Audit fields (created_at, updated_at) on all tables
- Soft delete with deleted_at timestamp
- Database transactions for consistency
- Connection pooling for performance
- Regular backup and recovery testing

